{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/varicocele/diagnosis/assessment/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"9a8077c8-bfa6-5d54-a316-af000153971c","slug":"assessment","fullItemName":"Assessment","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field a32a98b1-4092-4b30-8ea7-a73600fb3099 --><h2>How should I assess a man or boy with a suspected varicocele?</h2><!-- end field a32a98b1-4092-4b30-8ea7-a73600fb3099 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item fda18662-b592-48ef-97dd-a73600fb2e85 --><!-- begin field cf03181f-c116-4bd0-b912-a73600fb3099 --><ul><li>For information on the assessment of a man or boy with scrotal swelling, see the section on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/scrotal-pain-swelling/diagnosis/assessment/\">assessment</a> in the CKS topic on <a class=\"topic-reference external-reference\" href=\"/topics/scrotal-pain-swelling/\">Scrotal pain and swelling</a>.</li><li>The diagnosis of varicocele is usually <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/varicocele/diagnosis/clinical-features-of-varicocele/\">clinical</a>.<ul><li>Ultrasound with colour flow Doppler imaging may be useful if there is diagnostic uncertainty, or in larger men where thick scrotal skin, or increased amounts of scrotal tissue may make examination difficult. </li></ul></li><li>Examine all adolescents in the supine and standing positions to identify varicocele and assess whether testicular growth arrest has occurred.<ul><li>If the testes are symmetrical, examine the boy once annually through puberty and refer to a urologist if there is testicular asymmetry (left smaller than right) or impaired testicular growth occurs.</li></ul></li><li>Consider carrying out semen analyses in adults (on 2 or 3 separate occasions) and evaluation of serum follicle stimulating hormone (FSH) and testosterone levels to assess testicular function.<ul><li>Abnormal sperm production with an elevated FSH is consistent with impaired spermatogenesis.</li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field cf03181f-c116-4bd0-b912-a73600fb3099 --><!-- end item fda18662-b592-48ef-97dd-a73600fb2e85 -->","topic":{"id":"5977adfa-83aa-58a5-a712-0d4298766144","topicId":"466ec4b4-92f7-47d6-bfd7-b3b0ab41036b","topicName":"Varicocele","slug":"varicocele","lastRevised":"Last revised in April 2017","chapters":[{"id":"d0689845-07d1-5161-80e9-84ff77e5ad2b","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"d51b0e4c-521b-58bd-888f-f5dc2ebe6261","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"4580547c-b151-50d5-8dad-17550c8c7e58","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"4100bf94-3d55-5054-af0b-12a9a5df0db4","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"c7dd5fe2-22e0-5a96-a24e-68c9472ea09d","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"43488552-18c6-5033-977d-30d7c76c4dae","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"790589a4-32e2-5b89-9031-bdbbb1f5ff33","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"9a1cee3d-509b-5b2a-aef9-4371a66e36b7","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"891b532f-f746-5aef-8d40-5b97a41b8f40","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"f49848ab-01c1-52c1-8f76-c1b5da1fd757","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"b853589c-b4e3-548a-816e-c2926684bb4b","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"402f1a97-53c6-5574-852a-330f73910e5a","slug":"nice-quality-standards","fullItemName":"NICE quality standards"}]},{"id":"61d5d835-a558-5506-a1b7-5088d9d2b46b","fullItemName":"Background information","slug":"background-information","subChapters":[{"id":"90564a85-0d84-5962-ad99-45c2cd5ef4c1","slug":"definition","fullItemName":"Definition"},{"id":"da28bf23-66b4-5c24-8049-7a265285e0e9","slug":"prevalence","fullItemName":"Prevalence"},{"id":"5135d6f1-6d49-5321-99e6-e6c038a78dc9","slug":"cause","fullItemName":"Cause"},{"id":"162d49db-b71d-53dc-9ee4-0ebbf3210fcd","slug":"risks","fullItemName":"Risks"}]},{"id":"c9e25f17-4526-59b8-9d88-eed7e0e527a5","fullItemName":"Diagnosis","slug":"diagnosis","subChapters":[{"id":"9a8077c8-bfa6-5d54-a316-af000153971c","slug":"assessment","fullItemName":"Assessment"},{"id":"ce3fe174-add9-5c82-b0e9-1242a96030c9","slug":"clinical-features-of-varicocele","fullItemName":"Clinical features of varicocele"}]},{"id":"f3386f45-91ca-5634-b998-20abac53517c","fullItemName":"Management","slug":"management","subChapters":[{"id":"b0517ce5-e072-5590-b003-ffdc7eaf0395","slug":"management","fullItemName":"Scenario: Management"}]},{"id":"4ae01b73-c6b6-5516-aac3-ada400684bbe","fullItemName":"Supporting evidence","slug":"supporting-evidence","subChapters":[]},{"id":"e26fa119-c96d-5a26-886f-72687c971a79","fullItemName":"How this topic was developed","slug":"how-this-topic-was-developed","subChapters":[{"id":"5fc3d93d-d468-5e4d-84bb-55bcd963452e","slug":"search-strategy","fullItemName":"Search strategy"},{"id":"1cc51e68-e04e-58d0-b698-0daee006365c","slug":"stakeholder-engagement","fullItemName":"Stakeholder engagement"},{"id":"dd9fc3b0-f903-5bcd-a1e3-600c466b2744","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria"},{"id":"f524ccbb-83e4-53d7-a7a8-2053fa61bd7a","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers"},{"id":"448b62f3-2358-52f1-92ea-5808b58fc901","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"8b8fb73f-340e-5b80-ab8a-d5cff1126647","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"c9e25f17-4526-59b8-9d88-eed7e0e527a5","slug":"diagnosis","fullItemName":"Diagnosis"},"subChapters":[{"id":"e29fd467-2f70-54d2-b087-4ca5bc337c05","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-83d","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 2659fc60-cf64-4c58-877e-a74700914669 --><h3>Basis for recommendation</h3><!-- end field 2659fc60-cf64-4c58-877e-a74700914669 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 83d3fab7-cc70-4ff3-994e-a74700911fb6 --><!-- begin field 0f8babbd-c1c0-4381-8f53-a74700914669 --><p>These recommendations are based on the British Medical Journal (BMJ) best practice guide <em>Varicocele </em>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/varicocele/references/\">BMJ, 2016</a>], and the European Association of Urology (EAU) guideline <em>Male infertility</em> [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/varicocele/references/\">EAU, 2016a</a>].</p><p><strong>Semen analysis </strong>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/varicocele/references/\">BMJ, 2016</a>]</p><ul><li>Abnormal sperm concentration and/or abnormal sperm motility may identify patients who are more likely to benefit from surgical correction.</li><li>Semen analysis in adolescents is challenging and should be decided on an individual basis.</li></ul><!-- end field 0f8babbd-c1c0-4381-8f53-a74700914669 --><!-- end item 83d3fab7-cc70-4ff3-994e-a74700911fb6 -->","subChapters":[]}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3666801979"]}